# GitHub Copilot Compliance Playbook

Copy this folder into the root of a project that contains a checked-out Caracal codebase, so GitHub Copilot can run a truthful compliance and operations review.

## Use

1. Copy `AGENTS.md` into your project root (Copilot reads `AGENTS.md`), or paste it into Copilot Chat.
2. Point Copilot at the Caracal checkout you intend to adopt.
3. Ask it to run the compliance and operations review and produce the A–H report.
4. Review every "covered" claim against the cited path before relying on it.

## What it does

- Maps Caracal's actual controls to OWASP Agentic AI (ASI01–ASI10 + Agent Traceability), NIST AI RMF 100-1, the EU AI Act (2024/1689), SOC 2 Type II TSC, and AARM R1–R9.
- Cites an exact repository or docs path for every claim.
- Classifies every gap as a product, documentation, or operations gap.
- Makes no certification claims and separates Community Edition from Enterprise Edition.

This is a read-only review. The agent must not modify the codebase.
